					<p><b>Coordination</b>Among the major activities was the active participation of MM in several activities in the context of <b>Campus Plein Sud</b> (CPS) at the Free University of Brussels (ULB). We have scheduled the following together with SEDIF, which has the overall coordination of CPS:The participation in the <b>NGO Forum</b> on 29/02 in a tent we happily shared with a campaign to vaccinate livestock in Africa was quite productive. We met with a number of interesting people and had good conversations about work of MM, in particular on how sciences and arts in support of protecting the sea can be shared more effectively by teachers and teacher trainers from different countries. Flyers were distributed widely and some visitors of our booth are now on the distribution list of this progress report. A special thanks to Cleo Zhang, who volunteered to help staff the booth.</p>
