<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Mundis-Maris-International-Women-s-Day-Sustainable-Fisheries" title="Mundis Maris – International Women’s Day: Sustainable Fisheries" alt="link">Mundis Maris – International Women’s Day: Sustainable Fisheries</a></h2>

	
					<p>Today, 8 March, is<b> International Women’s Day</b>, so we would like to pay tribute to all girls and women, the majority of humanity, to be valued and respected for who and what they are. Among the countless others, meet a woman such as Awa Seye, with a life enriched by her tireless commitment to her own fishing community in Guet N’dar in St. Louis, Senegal, and all those on the coast: <a href="http://www.mundusmaris.org/index.php/en/projects/ms-en/158-mn-pilots-en?start=8" target="_blank">http://www.mundusmaris.org/index.php/en/projects/ms-en/158-mn-pilots-en?start=8</a></p>
